#########################################
#FOR ASSIGN INTERFACES to FIREWALL ZONES#
#########################################

# INVENTORY_HOST = all/list of inventory hosts separated by ",".
    # If "all" -> the configuration will be applied to all inventory hosts.
    # It is forbidden to include the same interface in several firewall zones.
    # If you want to apply the settings to a group of hosts or to all hosts, then make sure that each host has the interfaces specified in the #INTERFACE_LIST parameter.
    # Configurations like "all" have low priority over host groups (separated by ",") or individual hosts.
###
# FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT = name of the firewall zone template configured in the files "01_conf_custom_firewall_zones_templates" and "01_conf_standard_firewall_zones_templates".
###
# INTERFACE_LIST = list of interfaces, separated by ",".
###
#INVENTORY_HOST		#FIREWALL_ZONE_NAME_TMPLT		#INTERFACE_LIST
#all			public--TMPLT				ens1,ens2,ens3 (example)
#10.3.2.2		public--TMPLT				eth11,eth12,eth13 (example)
#10.1.2.3,10.1.2.4	zone1--TMPLT				eth0,eth1,ens01 (example)
